dataIdInfo.idAbs: This line vector dataset represents the faults used in the three-dimensional hydrogeologic framework model for the Rio Grande Transboundary region of New Mexico, Texas, USA and Northern Chihuahua, Mexico. Lines represent faults that were explicitly used in gridding hydrostratigraphic unit top elevations and thicknesses. The effect of faults shows up as abrupt changes in elevation or thickness of a hydrostratigraphic unit within the model grid.
dataIdInfo.idPurp: This dataset was created as part of a U.S. Geological Survey study, done in cooperation with the U.S. Bureau of Reclamation, to be used as the digital hydrogeologic input data for numerical simulation of the groundwater system of the Rio Grande transboundary region of New Mexico, Texas, USA and Northern Chihuahua, Mexico. The intended uses of this data set include, but are not limited to, natural resource modeling, mapping, and visualization applications.

attr.attrdef: Fault recency (age) describes if fault completely cuts the upper, middle, lower Santa Fe Group or the pre-Santa Fe Group rocks. The recency attribute lists the youngest unit that the fault cuts completely. Fault recency was determined through comparison with the USGS Quaternary fault database and through inspection of the structural offset of each fault shown on cross sections in the above reports.

attr.attrdef: Fault name, compiled from annotations on source maps and cross sections, combined with names listed in the Quaternary fault and fold database of the United States. Unnamed faults have a NULL value in this field.
